content.text: Alienated numbers (ℓ∅) do not belong to any known classical set of numbers, such as: - ℕ – natural numbers - ℤ – integers - ℚ – rational numbers - ℝ – real numbers - ℂ – complex numbers They also do not belong to extended systems such as: - Hypercomplex numbers (quaternions, octonions) - p-adic numbers - Algebraic constructions like fields or differential fields ℓ∅ does not satisfy the axioms of structures that define these sets — and does not adhere to their operations
